# Type 2 Example of Discreat Distribution

public class Mean_type_2 {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int sum = 0;
        int total = 0;
        
        int mean_value = 0;
        int a1[]={210,215,220,225,230,235,240,245};
        int a2[]={5,15,19,20,14,12,6,2};

        for(int i=0;i<a1.length;i++){

            a1[i] = a1[i] * a2[i];
        }

        for(int i=0;i<a1.length;i++){

        System.out.println(a1[i]+" ");
    }
        for(int i=0;i<a1.length;i++){
        	
       sum = sum+a1[i];
        }
        System.out.println("The Sum of Fixi is :"+sum);

        for(int i=0;i<a2.length;i++){

            total = total + a2[i];
        }
        System.out.println("the Total Sum of Xi is: "+total);

        System.out.println("You can Find the Mean By Using total of FiXi / by total of Fi");

        mean_value = sum / total;

        System.out.println("The Type 2 Mean Value answer is : "+mean_value+" Unites");

	}

}

-----------------------------------------
Output is :
1050 
3225 
4180 
4500 
3220 
2820 
1440 
490 
The Sum of Fixi is :20925
the Total Sum of Xi is: 93
You can Find the Mean By Using total of FiXi / by total of Fi
The Type 2 Mean Value answer is : 225 Unites


