# Type 3 Example of Continues Distribution

public class Mean_type_3 {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		        int[] midpoints = {5, 15, 25, 35, 45, 55, 65};
		        
		        int[] students = {5, 11, 17, 18, 13, 5, 2};

		        int totalMarks = 0;
		        int totalStudents = 0;

		        for (int i = 0; i < midpoints.length; i++) {
		            totalMarks += midpoints[i] * students[i];
		            totalStudents += students[i];
		        }

		        double mean = (double) totalMarks / totalStudents;

		        // Step 6: Print the result
		        System.out.println("Mean marks: " + mean);
		  
	}

}

----------------------------
Output is =
Mean marks: 31.47887323943662

